Mix the cheese, chorizo, beans, coriander and salt and freshly ground black pepper in a bowl.Spread the mixture onto one of the tortillas and top with the other.Heat a little oil in a frying pan and pan-fry the quesadilla for 2-3 minutes on each side.Meanwhile, for the salad, mix all the ingredients together in a bowl and season with salt and pepper. Garnish with more fresh coriander.To serve, transfer the quesadilla to a plate and serve the salad alongside.